{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/FillShapeView\/monospacedDigit()"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"nonisolated","kind":"attribute"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"monospacedDigit","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"some","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"View","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"},{"text":"\n","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Return Value","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"return-value"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A view whose child views’ fonts use fixed-width numeric","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"characters, while leaving other characters proportionally spaced.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"},{"content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using fixed-width digits allows you to easily align numbers of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"same size in a table-like arrangement. This feature is also known as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"“tabular figures” or “tabular numbers.”"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This modifier only affects numeric characters, and leaves all other"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"characters unchanged."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example shows the effect of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"monospacedDigit()"},{"type":"text","text":" on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"multiple child views. The example consists of two "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/VStack","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" views"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"inside an "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/HStack","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Each "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VStack"},{"type":"text","text":" contains two "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Button","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" views, with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the second "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VStack"},{"type":"text","text":" applying the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"monospacedDigit()"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier to its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"contents. As a result, the digits in the buttons in the trailing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VStack"},{"type":"text","text":" are the same width, which in turn gives the buttons equal widths."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["var body: some View {","    HStack(alignment: .top) {","        VStack(alignment: .leading) {","            Button(\"Delete 111 messages\") {}","            Button(\"Delete 222 messages\") {}","        }","        VStack(alignment: .leading) {","            Button(\"Delete 111 messages\") {}","            Button(\"Delete 222 messages\") {}","        }","        .monospacedDigit()","    }","    .padding()","    .navigationTitle(\"monospacedDigit() Child Views\")","}"]},{"inlineContent":[],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a child view’s base font doesn’t support fixed-width digits, the font"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"remains unchanged."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/fillshapeview\/monospaceddigit()"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Op